Taking average fitted values:\[
\overline{\hat{Y}} = \frac{1}{n} \sum_{=1}^n \hat{Y}_i = \frac{1}{n} \sum_{=1}^n (\hat{\beta}_0 + \hat{\beta}_1 X_i) = \hat{\beta}_0 + \hat{\beta}_1 \bar{X}
\]Since \(\hat{\beta}_0 = \bar{Y} - \hat{\beta}_1 \bar{X}\):\[
\overline{\hat{Y}} = (\bar{Y} - \hat{\beta}_1 \bar{X}) + \hat{\beta}_1 \bar{X} = \bar{Y}
\]Equivalently, \(X = \bar{X}\):\[
\hat{Y}(\bar{X}) = \hat{\beta}_0 + \hat{\beta}_1 \bar{X} = \bar{Y}
\]Conclusion: OLS fitted line passes point \((\bar{X}, \bar{Y})\).

Since \(\sum_{=1}^n \hat{u}_i = 0\):\[
\boxed{\bar{\hat{u}} = \frac{1}{n} \sum_{=1}^n \hat{u}_i = 0}
\]

